input_str: I usually tend to cover artists coming from the Third Reich era, but this time I would like to make an exception with this particular painter, in part because he is an artist from one of my favourite periods in art history (the Turn of the Century period to be accurate) and in part because he is credited as being the ‘inventor’ (discoverer I should say) of camouflage for the military industry.
